

	 
        We go to liberate not to conquer. We will not fly our flags in their country [...] We are entering Iraq to free a people and the only flag which will be flown in that ancient land is their own. Show respect for them. [...] Iraq is steeped in history. It is the site of the Garden of Eden, of the Great Flood and the birthplace of Abraham. Tread lightly there. [...] You will be embarrassed by their hospitality even though they have nothing.   urlLink This speech  by Lieutenant Colonel Tim Collins to a British battalion is really encouraging, and hopefully all the soldiers, whether they heard it or not, will act accordingly.
     
    
